  "time_ut": 1656338358,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0d86\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0da9\u0dd2\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dbb \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Take immediate action to import fuel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa has instructed officials to take immediate action to import fuel using the money available in the country and the Governor of the Central Bank has agreed to pay the companies for the fuel supply with a cash plan, the Presidential Media Unit said.",
        "It was decided to provide funds from the Central Bank and the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation to restore the supply of fuel and to consult with the relevant parent companies to obtain fuel within a grace period if the credit opening procedure followed so far is not available. According to the Presidential Media Unit, the President has instructed to formulate a formal program to maintain the system.",
        "He was speaking at a discussion between the President and representatives of major companies that have been importing fuel to Sri Lanka for a long time at the President's House in Fort this morning (27).",
        "Representatives pointed out the need for the Governor of the Central Bank and the Secretary to the Treasury to directly engage in discussions with parent companies, international banks and financial institutions supplying fuel.",
        "Kanchana Wijesekera, Minister of Power and Energy; Gamini Senarath, Secretary to the President; Lalith Weeratunga, Chief Adviser to the President; Anura Dissanayake, Chief of Staff to the President; Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe, Governor, Central Bank; And heads of energy and fiscal institutions were also present."
      ],
